				'endtime','00:29:25.16:00');
		}
		catch (e) {
			//document.write(e);
		}</script><p><strong>Atcheson Hench: </strong>Do all&mdash;do many people use the word "chapping" for having children.
						Somebody said, "We ain't nigh done chapping yet."</p>
<p><strong>William Faulkner: </strong>That's quite colloquial. You hear that only in the remote hill
						country. People that&mdash;that have no&mdash;where there are no Negroes and their
						speech is not corrupted by&mdash;by Negro inflections and the Negro usage of words.
