<p><strong>Atcheson Hench: </strong>You've never hunted.</p>
<p><strong>Edward Stephenson: </strong>No, I'm not a hunter.</p>
<p><strong>Atcheson Hench: </strong>Well, Mr. Faulkner is. He's heard the sound of dogs.</p>
<p><strong>William Faulkner: </strong>That means they were&mdash;they were on game. They bayed once, then they
						recognized Tomey's Turl, a friend, so they quit.</p>
<p><strong>Edward Stephenson: </strong>I see.</p>
<p><strong>William Faulkner: </strong>They just caught up with him to lick his hand, to run along with
						him.</p>
<hr>
<a name="wfaudio11_1.44">&nbsp;</a><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">
