<p><strong>William Faulkner: </strong>Yes, they pronounce "supple," "soople."</p>
<p><strong>Edward Stephenson: </strong>I've heard the pronunciation of the adjective as "soople." This is a
						verb in the past tense, "soopled."</p>
<p><strong>William Faulkner: </strong>Yes, that's right. To&mdash;to "soople" is to do something rapid and
